Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Unroll the @puff pastry sheet{1} and lay onto a
#baking tray{} lined with #baking paper{}. Prick the pastry all over with a
#fork{}. Pop onto the top shelf of the oven and cook until lightly golden all
over, ~{12-15%minutes}. Once cooked, remove from the oven and set to one side.

> TIP: If the middle has risen, gently flatten the pastry with the back of a
> spoon!

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Heat a
drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} over medium heat. Once hot, add the
onion and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook,
stirring occasionally, until softened and starting to colour, ~{5-6%minutes}.
Meanwhile, thinly slice the @tomato{2%medium}(thinly sliced) and grate the
@mature cheddar cheese{30%g}(grated).

Once the onion is soft, transfer to a #mixing bowl{} and stir in the cheddar
cheese and @crème fraîche{150%g}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{pinch}. When the pastry is out of the oven, use a #spoon{} to spread
the cheese and onion crème fraîche all over it. Leave a 2-3cm border on all
four sides! Top with the sliced tomato and sprinkle over the
@dried oregano{1}(sprinkled over) (use as much or as little as you like!).

Bake the tart once again on the top shelf of the oven until the tomato is
cooked and the cheese has melted, ~{10-15%minutes}. In the meantime, pop a
large #saucepan{} of water on to boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch} for the
green beans.

Trim the @green beans{150}(trimmed). Halve the @lemon{1/2}. When the water is
boiling, add the green beans to the pan and cook until tender, ~{5%minutes}.
Drain in a #sieve{} and set to one side.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix together the @wholegrain mustard{1/2},
@olive oil{1}(for the dressing), a squeeze of lemon juice to taste and a
pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Once your tart is out of the oven,
slice into portions and share between your plates. Pop the green beans
alongside the tart and drizzle over the mustard vinaigrette. Enjoy!